member.summary:
BlockchainRpcOptions values are mostly required for proper blockchain interaction to occur
via the MCWrapper.RPC client.


    The MCWrapper RPC client requires the following BlockchainProfileOptions be assigned a valid value
        ChainUseSsl;
        ChainSslPath 
            (ChainSslPath only required to be assigned a file path value if ChainUseSsl is true, 
             otherwise ChainSslPath can be empty string "");
        ChainUsername;
        ChainPassword;
        ChainName;
        ChainRpcPort;
        ChainAdminAddress;
        ChainHostname;

Multichain blockchain name as declared in the params.dat file;
ChainName value is required for the RPC client to function as expected when using methods that infer the blockchain name value;
When using methods that support using the blockchain name explicitly with the RPC client,the ChainName value is not necessary or required.

Your blockchain node administror's public key. In v2 we are only supporting a 
single node administrator per application instance.


    ChainAdminAddress is required for the RPC client to function as expected;

Local or remote file path to a copy of the same SSL certificate that is securing the current node the application is interacting with.
ChainSslPath is not required for the RPC client to function as expected;
Please note: If the ChainUseSsl value is true, the ChainSslPath value MUST be populated and accurate. When starting an HTTPS blockahin ensure you pass the -rpcssl flag and properly configure your multichain.conf file properly to support HTTPS connections.

